msgid "Rebuilding a Debian package starts with getting its source code. The easiest way is to use the <command>apt-get source <replaceable>package-name</replaceable></command> command. This command requires a <literal>deb-src</literal> line in the <filename>/etc/apt/sources.list</filename> file, and up-to-date index files (i.e. <command>apt-get update</command>). These conditions should already be met if you followed the instructions from the chapter dealing with APT configuration (see <xref linkend=\"sect.apt-sources.list\" />). Note, however, that you will be downloading the source packages from the Debian version mentioned in the <literal>deb-src</literal> line."
